cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.SD, cs.MM

This paper deals with regularization and sparsification of deep neural networks, specifically quaternion-based networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions applications in audio processing, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound). Finally, the paper discusses the need for compact networks, which could be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia).
